## Examples

The following examples demonstrate how to configure the AI Semantic Caching policy for different use cases.

### LLM proxy with JSONPath extraction

This example caches OpenAI-compatible chat completions by extracting only the last message content from the request payload. The `promptExpression` uses JSONPath to isolate the relevant text for semantic comparison.

```json
{
  "name": "AI Semantic Caching",
  "enabled": true,
  "policy": "ai-semantic-caching",
  "configuration": {
    "modelName": "ai-model-text-embedding-resource",
    "vectorStoreName": "vector-store-redis-resource",
    "promptExpression": "{#jsonPath(#request.content, '$.messages[-1:].content')}",
    "cacheCondition": "{#response.status >= 200 && #response.status < 300}",
    "parameters": [
      {
        "key": "retrieval_context_key",
        "value": "{#context.attributes['api']}",
        "encode": true
      }
    ]
  }
}
```

**Key configuration details:**
- `promptExpression`: Extracts the content of the last message in the chat history
- `cacheCondition`: Caches only successful responses (2xx status codes)
- `parameters`: Uses the API ID as metadata for cache scoping, with encoding enabled for privacy

### Custom cache condition

This example demonstrates a stricter cache condition that stores only responses with a 200 status code.

```json
{
  "name": "AI Semantic Caching",
  "enabled": true,
  "policy": "ai-semantic-caching",
  "configuration": {
    "modelName": "ai-model-text-embedding-resource",
    "vectorStoreName": "vector-store-redis-resource",
    "promptExpression": "{#request.content}",
    "cacheCondition": "{#response.status == 200}",
    "parameters": []
  }
}
```

**Key configuration details:**
- `promptExpression`: Uses the entire request body for semantic comparison
- `cacheCondition`: Caches only responses with exactly 200 status code
- `parameters`: No metadata filtering applied

### Multi-parameter metadata filtering

This example shows how to scope the cache using multiple metadata parameters for fine-grained control.

```json
{
  "name": "AI Semantic Caching",
  "enabled": true,
  "policy": "ai-semantic-caching",
  "configuration": {
    "modelName": "ai-model-text-embedding-resource",
    "vectorStoreName": "vector-store-redis-resource",
    "promptExpression": "{#request.content}",
    "cacheCondition": "{#response.status >= 200 && #response.status < 300}",
    "parameters": [
      {
        "key": "api_id",
        "value": "{#context.attributes['api']}",
        "encode": false
      },
      {
        "key": "plan_id",
        "value": "{#context.attributes['plan']}",
        "encode": false
      },
      {
        "key": "user_id",
        "value": "{#context.attributes['user-id']}",
        "encode": true
      }
    ]
  }
}
```

**Key configuration details:**
- `parameters`: Combines API, plan, and user context for cache isolation
- `encode`: Set to `true` for the user ID to hash sensitive information using MurmurHash3